# Cursor Rules for AI Research Documentation
name: "AI Research Documentation Rules"
version: 1.0
description: "Rules for managing and updating the AI research documentation"

# Documentation Structure Rules
structure:
  - All documentation files should be in Markdown format
  - Place new documentation in appropriate /docs subdirectories
  - Include front matter in all markdown files
  - Maintain consistent section structure
  - Sort dependencies alphabetically in configuration files

# Content Format
format:
  writing:
    - Capitalize proper nouns (e.g., "Markdown", "Ruby", "Jekyll")
    - Avoid redundant words (e.g., "CLI interface", "API interface")
    - Use consistent terminology throughout
  sections:
    - title: Required at top level
    - description: Brief overview
    - features: Listed under "Key Features"
    - links: GitHub/Documentation/Website as applicable
    
  frontMatter:
    required:
      - layout
      - title
      - nav_order
    optional:
      - has_children
      - parent

# Section Template
template: |
  ---
  layout: default
  title: Section Title
  nav_order: [number]
  ---

  # [Section Title]

  Brief description of the section.

  ## [Tool/Framework Name]
  - **GitHub**: [org/repo](https://github.com/org/repo)
  - **Documentation**: [Docs](https://docs.example.com)
  - **Description**: Concise description
  - **Key Features**:
    - Feature 1
    - Feature 2
    - Feature 3

# Update Instructions
instructions:
  - Verify GitHub links before adding
  - Keep descriptions concise and factual
  - Standardize feature lists under "Key Features"
  - Include relevant links (GitHub, docs, demos)
  - Maintain alphabetical order within sections
  - Add front matter to all new pages

# Categories
categories:
  - AI Agents
  - AI Models
  - Development Tools
  - Documentation Tools
  - IDEs and Editors

# Search Terms
searchTerms:
  - AI
  - Machine Learning
  - Documentation
  - Tools
  - Frameworks
  - Models 